import{_ as e,c as t,o as r,a4 as c}from"./chunks/framework.DdddRsJj.js";const h=JSON.parse('{"title":"副词","description":"","frontmatter":{"title":"副词"},"headers":[],"relativePath":"language/english/adverb.md","filePath":"language/english/adverb.md"}'),n={name:"language/english/adverb.md"};function a(s,o,d,l,p,g){return r(),t("div",null,[...o[0]||(o[0]=[c('<p>修饰性词类，一般用于修饰动词、形容词或副词。也可修饰名词或句子。【修饰】，可理解为用其他概念<mark>从某些方面更具体得</mark>表达某个事物。</p><h2 id="作用" tabindex="-1">作用 <a class="header-anchor" href="#作用" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;作用&quot;">​</a></h2><h3 id="修饰" tabindex="-1">修饰 <a class="header-anchor" href="#修饰" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;修饰&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li>修饰名词，形容词或副词时，常位于其<mark>前面</mark>。</li></ul><blockquote><p><strong>Hardly anyone</strong> believed him.<br> It&#39;s <strong>quite some time</strong> since I wtote to her.<br></p></blockquote><blockquote><p>The weather is <strong>pleasantly warm</strong>.<br> I am <strong>terribly tired</strong>.<br></p></blockquote><blockquote><p>He falls <strong>far behind</strong> in his studies.<br> The engine runs <strong>very quietly</strong>.<br></p></blockquote><p><strong>介词短语</strong>可充当副词，因而副词可修饰介词短语。</p><blockquote><p>He left <strong>shortly after the meeting</strong>.<br></p></blockquote><p>一些常见的搭配：<code>well over my head</code>，<code>well within the time(完全在规定时间内)</code>，<code>right in front of you(就在你前面)</code>，<code>far in the future</code>。</p><ul><li>修饰句子时，通常是某些<strong>评注性</strong>或<strong>逻辑连接</strong>的词语，如<code>finally</code>，<code>actually</code>等等。需要<mark>逗号</mark>把它和句子隔开来。</li></ul><blockquote><p><strong>Certainly</strong>, I will stand by you forever.<br> &gt; <strong>Therefore</strong>, the film is less than perfect. (因而)<br></p></blockquote><ul><li>修饰动词，副词最常见的是修饰<strong>动词</strong>，此时其位置较为灵活。</li></ul><p>对于表达动作的<strong>方式或状态</strong>的副词（<mark>方式类</mark>），一般<mark>置于后面</mark>。尽可能接近动词，但让位于其他更重要的成分（因为是修饰类）。</p><blockquote><p>He kept quiet <strong>resolutely</strong>.<br> They elected him chairman <strong>unanimously</strong>.<br></p></blockquote><p>当然，如果副词距离所修饰的动词太远，可见其<mark>置于动词前面</mark>。</p><blockquote><p>I <strong>happily pronounce</strong> you man and wife.<br></p></blockquote><p>多个此类的副词可用 <code>and</code> 或 <code>or</code> 连接。一般遵循【更具体在前】或【更短在前】原则。</p><blockquote><p>He spoke <strong>shortly and carefully</strong>.<br></p></blockquote><hr><p>对于强调<strong>语气、频率、范围、程度</strong>类（<mark>限定类</mark>）的副词，通常紧跟在<mark>行为动词前面</mark>，但在助动词、情态动词、be 动词后面。</p><blockquote><p>I <strong>badly need</strong> a drink. // 语气<br> You <strong>are always</strong> late. // 频率<br> I <strong>only heard</strong> about the accident yesterday. // 范围<br> The project is <strong>almost finished</strong>. // 程度<br></p></blockquote><p>某些表达【相对时间】类副词，如<code>already</code>，<code>just</code>，<code>still</code>，<code>now</code>等等，也是这种位置放置。</p><blockquote><p>I <strong>have just seen</strong> the local paper.<br></p></blockquote><blockquote><p>副词单词一般放在<mark>否定助动词前</mark>，always 除外。<br> He <strong>doesn&#39;t always</strong> leave before 6 o&#39;clock.<br></p></blockquote><hr><p>对于<strong>时间或地点</strong>类的副词，通常置于句首或句尾。</p><blockquote><p><strong>Yesterday we</strong> went to see a film.<br></p></blockquote><hr><p>通常的，多个副词的顺序原则是，<mark>更具体的在前</mark>，不具体的在后。一般表现为：方式动词、地点副词、时间副词。</p><blockquote><p>She sang <strong>beautifully in the hall last night</strong>.<br> Come to see me <strong>at 3 o&#39;clock in the afternoon</strong>.<br></p></blockquote><p>当然，对于某些<mark>经常接地点</mark>的不及物动词，如<code>go</code>，<code>live</code>，<code>run</code>等来说，后面的地点副词位于方式副词前。</p><blockquote><p>I ran <strong>to school alone</strong> because I was late.<br> They went <strong>to school hurriedly</strong> after the breakfast.<br></p></blockquote><hr><p>对于<code>yet</code>，<code>any more</code>，<code>too</code>，<code>as well</code>等词，一般置于句末。</p><blockquote><p>They are not selling it <strong>any more</strong>.<br> I haven&#39;t read the book <strong>yet</strong>.<br></p></blockquote><p>程度副词<code>enough</code>通常在<mark>形容词之后</mark>。</p><blockquote><p>We are fortunate <strong>enough</strong> to have a car of our own.<br></p></blockquote><p><code>probably</code> 在否定句中可<mark>置于助动词或 be 动词之前</mark>。</p><blockquote><p>I <strong>probably</strong> won’t see you. // I **will probably not ** see you.<br></p></blockquote><h3 id="其他" tabindex="-1">其他 <a class="header-anchor" href="#其他" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;其他&quot;">​</a></h3><h4 id="表达状态" tabindex="-1">表达状态 <a class="header-anchor" href="#表达状态" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;表达状态&quot;">​</a></h4><p>可作为<strong>表语</strong>或<strong>宾语补足语</strong>来表达状态。</p><blockquote><p>Time is <strong>up</strong>. // 时间到了<br> Everything is <strong>over</strong> between them.<br> Let the dog <strong>out</strong>.<br></p></blockquote><h4 id="后置定语" tabindex="-1">后置定语 <a class="header-anchor" href="#后置定语" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;后置定语&quot;">​</a></h4><p>通常是时间或地点副词。</p><blockquote><p>The meeting <strong>today</strong> lasted three hours.<br> Put the book on the shelf <strong>above</strong>.<br></p></blockquote><h4 id="介词宾语" tabindex="-1">介词宾语 <a class="header-anchor" href="#介词宾语" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;介词宾语&quot;">​</a></h4><p>副词可位于介词后面，形成介词短语。有<code>from abroad(从国外)</code>，<code>near here(在附件)</code>，<code>since then(从那时起)</code>，<code>till recently(直到最近)</code>等等。</p><blockquote><p><strong>Since then</strong>，robots have joined the fight.<br></p></blockquote><h2 id="辨析" tabindex="-1">辨析 <a class="header-anchor" href="#辨析" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;辨析&quot;">​</a></h2><h3 id="形式接近-含义不同" tabindex="-1">形式接近，含义不同 <a class="header-anchor" href="#形式接近-含义不同" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;形式接近，含义不同&quot;">​</a></h3><p><code>close(靠近地)</code> &amp; <code>closely(仔细地)</code></p><blockquote><p>Sit <strong>close</strong> to the table, please.<br> Watch my mouth <strong>closely</strong>.<br></p></blockquote><p><code>free(免费地)</code> &amp; <code>freely(自由的)</code></p><blockquote><p>we go into the concert <strong>free</strong>.<br> I want to wander <strong>freely</strong> over the hill.<br></p></blockquote><p><code>dead(完全地)</code> &amp; <code>deadly(死一般地)</code></p><blockquote><p>The train stopped <strong>dead</strong>.<br> His face is <strong>deadly</strong> white.<br></p></blockquote><p><code>late(晚)</code> &amp; <code>lately(近来)</code></p><blockquote><p>He arrived <strong>late</strong> this moring.<br> What have you been doing <strong>lately</strong>.<br></p></blockquote><p><code>direct(径直)</code> &amp; <code>directly(立刻)</code></p><blockquote><p>The plane goes <strong>dirent</strong> to the Beijing.<br> I hope you will answer me <strong>dirently</strong>.<br></p></blockquote><p><code>most(最)</code> &amp; <code>mostly(大多数地)</code></p><blockquote><p>You are <strong>a most unusual</strong> man.<br> They are <strong>mostly</strong> from ShangHai.<br></p></blockquote><p><code>wide(充分地)</code> &amp; <code>widely(广泛地)</code></p><blockquote><p>I was <strong>wide</strong> wake all night.<br> He was <strong>widely</strong> known in our community.<br></p></blockquote><p><code>high(高)</code> &amp; <code>highly(很)</code></p><blockquote><p>Does he jump <strong>high</strong> ?<br> &gt; <strong>Highly</strong> recommended location is Little Manly.<br></p></blockquote><p><code>deep(深)</code> &amp; <code>deeply(强烈地)</code></p><blockquote><p>They danced <strong>deep</strong> into the night.<br> I was <strong>deeply</strong> touched by the film.<br></p></blockquote><p><code>near(附近)</code> &amp; <code>nearly(几乎)</code></p><blockquote><p>Spring draws <strong>near</strong>.<br> He can play <strong>nearly</strong> every musical instrument.<br></p></blockquote><h3 id="含义接近-用法不同" tabindex="-1">含义接近，用法不同 <a class="header-anchor" href="#含义接近-用法不同" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;含义接近，用法不同&quot;">​</a></h3><p><code>ago</code>：从现在算起的【以前】。 <code>before</code>：从过去或将来算起的【以前】。可泛指【以前做过某事】。</p><blockquote><p>I met her three years <strong>ago</strong>.<br> I told you I had met her three years <strong>before</strong>.<br></p></blockquote><hr><p><code>very</code>：通常修饰形容词或副词，如<code>very good</code>，<code>very exciting book</code>。 <code>much</code>：可修饰不可数名词或动词，或比较级。<code>much time</code>，<code>make much of(充分理解)</code>，<code>not thing much of(感觉很一般)</code>。</p><p>表达确定性方面，<code>very</code> 要比 <code>much</code> 更强。</p><hr><p><code>too</code>：【也】，用于肯定句，常位于句末，可用有逗号。 <code>either</code>：【也】，用于否定句，只位于句末。</p><blockquote><p>Nice to meet you, <strong>too</strong>.<br> I did not <strong>either</strong>.<br></p></blockquote><hr><p><code>enough</code> &amp; <code>too</code></p><p>形容词性用法【太多的】：<code>enough + 复数名词或不可数</code>，<code>too many + 可数复数</code>或<code>too much + 不可数</code>。</p><blockquote><p>I have not <strong>enough tools</strong> to do this job.<br> There is <strong>too much rain</strong> this year.<br></p></blockquote><p>副词性用法【过度地，太】：<code>adj/adv + enough</code>，<code>too + adj/adv</code>。</p><blockquote><p>She is not <strong>old enough</strong> to drive a car.<br> It is <strong>too aloud</strong>.<br></p></blockquote><hr><p><code>so...that</code>：<code>so</code>一般后接形容词或副词。<code>so + adj/adv (+ a/an + noun)</code>，<code>so many/few + nouns</code>，<code>so much/little + noun</code>。</p><p><code>such...that</code>：<code>such</code>一般接名词。<code>such + a/an/adj noun</code>。</p><blockquote><p>He ran <strong>so fast that</strong> I could not catch up with him. <br> It was <strong>such a bad weather that</strong> I had to stay at home.<br> He is <strong>so good a student</strong> that we all like him.<br></p></blockquote><p><code>so little</code>表示【少的】，而<code>such little</code>表示【小的】。</p><hr><p><code>almost</code> &amp; <code>nearly</code></p><p>意为【几乎】，两者几乎等同。可用于修饰<code>every</code>，<code>all</code>等词。都可用于否定句。</p><blockquote><p><strong>Almost/Nearly all</strong> the students went there.<br></p></blockquote><p>在否定副词，如<code>any</code>，<code>no</code>，<code>nothing</code>，<code>nobody</code>，<code>never</code>等前用<code>almost</code>，不用<code>nearly</code>。</p><blockquote><p>I <strong>almost never</strong> see her.<br></p></blockquote><p><code>nearly</code>前可用程度副词修饰，如<code>very/pretty nearly(几乎)</code>，<code>not nearly(完全不)</code>。</p><blockquote><p>The car is <strong>very nearly</strong> new.<br> It is <strong>not nearly</strong> as cold as yesterday.<br></p></blockquote><hr><p><code>fairly</code> &amp; <code>rather</code></p><p>【相当地】。通常前者修饰【好的，令人愉悦的】<mark>形容词</mark>，后者修饰【坏的，令人感觉不愉快的】形容词。</p><blockquote><p>She is a <strong>fairly good</strong> singer.<br> She has a <strong>rather poor</strong> opinion of your written work.<br></p></blockquote><p><code>rather</code>可与<code>too</code>连用或修饰比较级。</p><blockquote><p>These shoes are <strong>rather too</strong> big.<br> She drives <strong>rather faster</strong> than she ought.<br></p></blockquote><p>英国人用<code>rather</code>修饰自己感兴趣的事物。</p><blockquote><p>I find this subject <strong>rather interesting</strong>.<br></p></blockquote><hr><p><code>quite</code> &amp; <code>rather</code></p><p>修饰名词，意为【十分】。两者几乎等同。</p><blockquote><p>It was <strong>quite/rather a shock</strong> to see my face on the screen.<br></p></blockquote><p>若名词前有形容词。</p><blockquote><p>It is <strong>a rather bad story</strong>.<br> = It is <strong>rather a bad story</strong>.<br></p></blockquote><hr><p><code>too much</code> &amp; <code>much too</code></p><p><code>too much</code>中心词为<code>much</code>，意为【太多的】或【太】。作形容词修饰不可数名词，作副词可修饰动词。</p><blockquote><p>You have give me <strong>too much (something)</strong>.<br> She is <strong>too much brothered</strong> by the noise.<br></p></blockquote><p><code>much too</code>中心词为<code>too</code>，意为【太】。副词性，修饰形容词或副词，但不修饰动词。</p><blockquote><p>The lane is <strong>much too narrow</strong> for car to pass.<br></p></blockquote><p>在<code>too many/few</code>前用<code>far</code>而不用<code>much</code>修饰。</p><blockquote><p>We have got <strong>far too many opportunities</strong> after graduation.<br></p></blockquote><hr><p><code>alone</code> &amp; <code>lonely</code></p><p><code>alone</code>作形容词表【孤生一人的】，指形体的单独。也可用作副词，放在动词后面。</p><blockquote><p><strong>She alone</strong> took care of her five children.<br> After the party he <strong>went</strong> home <strong>alone</strong>.<br></p></blockquote><p><code>lonely</code>只作为形容词，表精神上的【孤独】或【偏僻的】。</p><blockquote><p>He <strong>lived alone</strong> in <strong>a lonely house</strong>, but he didn&#39;t feel <strong>lonely</strong>.<br></p></blockquote><hr><p><code>a bit</code> &amp; <code>a little</code></p><p>副词，意为【一点儿，稍微】。</p><blockquote><p>The problem is <strong>a bit/little difficult</strong> for the little boy.<br></p></blockquote><p><code>not a bit</code>意为【一点也不】，<code>not a little</code>意为【完全地】。</p><blockquote><p>He does <strong>not</strong> mind <strong>a bit</strong>.<br> He did <strong>not</strong> praise her <strong>a little</strong>. // 非常赞美<br></p></blockquote><p>表达【一点也不】的短语还可以是<code>not in the least/slightest</code>.</p><hr><p><code>as far as</code> &amp; <code>as long as</code></p><p><code>as/so far as</code>可表距离，后接名词，意为【远至...】。</p><blockquote><p>He didn&#39;t go <strong>so/as far as the bridge</strong>.<br></p></blockquote><p><code>as far as</code> 可用于【就...而言】，<code>as far as possible</code>为【尽可能地】。</p><blockquote><p><strong>As far as I know</strong> he will be away for three months.<br> I will help you <strong>as far as possible</strong>.<br></p></blockquote><p><code>as/so long as</code>意为【只要】，用作连词，引导让步状语从句。</p><blockquote><p><strong>As long as</strong> you are happy, it doesn&#39;t matter what you do.<br></p></blockquote><p><code>as long ago as</code> 意为【早在...】。</p>',144)])])}const u=e(n,[["render",a]]);export{h as __pageData,u as default};
